<h1>
The "NetBSD/amiga Beginner's Guide to TCP/IP Networking
 and Networking-FAQ", 2nd Edition
</h1>

After quite some time, I've had the time to make an update on the
Networking FAQ to reflect the chances made in NetBSD V1.2.
The second edition contains lots of smaller enhancements, as well as
sections on the following topic:
<P>

<UL>
<LI> Arcnet, <A HREF="nwf_18.html">technical stuff</A> and <a
     href="nwf_24.html">setup</a> 
<LI> Setting up <A HREF="nwf_28.html">SLIP</A> and <A HREF="nwf_26.html">PPP</A> both manually and automatic (using <A HREF="nwf_29.html">bsddip</A>
     and <A HREF="nwf_27.html">chat</A>)
<LI> Setting up the system as <A HREF="nwf_35.html">NIS client</A>
<LI> Setting up <A HREF="nwf_51.html">`/net'</A> with amd
<LI> List of URLs for <A HREF="nwf_63.html">secure telnet/rlogin sessions</A>, <A
     HREF="nwf_64.html">WWW-servers</A> and <A
     HREF="nwf_65.html">-proxies</A> as well as <A
     HREF="nwf_66.html">firewalls</A>.
<LI> How to deal with <A HREF="nwf_68.html">'silo overflows'</A>
<LI> What is <A HREF="nwf_69.html">proxy-arp</A>, how to use it
</UL>
 

The FAQ is
available from <A HREF="ftp://ftp.uni-regensburg.de/">ftp.uni-regensburg.de</A> in the directory
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.uni-regensburg.de/pub/NetBSD-Amiga/docs/Networking-FAQ">/pub/NetBSD-Amiga/docs/Networking-FAQ</A>. Available versions are:
<P>

<UL>
<LI> Texinfo-source (<A HREF="nwf.texi">nwf.texi</A>)
<LI> PostScript (<A HREF="nwf.ps">nwf.ps</A>)
<LI> Info-format (<A HREF="nwf.info">nwf.info</A>, nwf.info-*)
<LI> Plain ASCII (<A HREF="nwf.txt">nwf.txt</A>, <A HREF="pic1.txt">pic1.txt</A>, <A HREF="pic2.txt">pic2.txt</A>, <A HREF="pic3.txt">pic3.txt</A>)
<LI> HTML (<A HREF="nwf_toc.html">nwf_toc.html</A>, nwf_*.html)
<LI> <A HREF="NWF.tar.gz">Everything</A> in a single .tar.gz file (350kB)
</UL>

The HTML-version is also reachable via WWW:
<A HREF="">http://rfhs8012.fh-regensburg.de/~feyrer/NetBSD/NWF/nwf_toc.html</A>.
<P>

This should be enough versions to fit everyone's needs. ;-) If someone
wants to recreate the above versions from scratch, the Makefile, a
self-written script and (enhanced :-) texi2html have also been put onto the
FTP-Server. A simple "make all" should rebuild everything.
<P>

Please email any comments, etc. to hubert.feyrer@rz.uni-regensburg.de.
<P>


Hubert<BR>
Regensburg, December 22nd, 1996<P>


